sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2004013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Expressed in Stylophora pistillata, was evolving independently from the rest of coral chromoproteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In this way, a brief step to confirm the chromoprotein expression is purifying it, so to facilitate this process we fuse a improved version of the sequence (BBa_K2004004) that codifies to pink chromoprotein with another registered part, the poly his tag (BBa_K844000). The last version of this chromoprotein(BBa_K1684000), designed by the previous Biosint team, was analyzed according to its sequence and all the parameter that must meet to be part of a standardized biobrick. This device (BBa_K2004013) allows to test the fusion, because contains a constitutive promoter and a RBS upstream and the double terminator downstream.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is a improved and correct version of the protein spispink, to be able to use like a biobrick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Marco V. Lincango Y.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K844000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 10x-Histidine tag with double stop codon TAATAA to allow for better extraction of tagged products and protein termination in a single part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathleen Miller

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2004004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: spisPink: Pink chromoprotein optimized for E.coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is an improved version of BBa_K1684000, designed by BIOSINT_Mexico previous team.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Chromoproteins are a collection of proteins that express pigments. This protein, expressed in Stylophora pistillata, was evolving independently from the rest of coral chromoproteins.
The protein has a maximum absorption of 560 nm. This characteristic confers a blue shift by at least 14 nanometers in comparison to other known coral chromoproteins, inducing the production of pink color.
This basic part can be used for whatever E. coli strain and is able to use with RFC 10 assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence was analyzed by softwars and we noticed some mistakes into the sequence to be part of the standardized biobrick library. This new version of the part contains all the specifications required to be a functional biobrick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Marco V. Lincango Y.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
